 d to speak into microphones and we've typically had one roaming microphone
  for questions. The speaker\, Ginni Rometty and I should be miked up and w
 e could use a handheld for FGCU Board Chair\, Michael Wynn\, who will intr
 oduce the speaker. We can use that same handheld for the question period. 
  It also needs to be recorded.\n\nThanks for your work.\n\n\n\nEric B. Den
 t\, Ph.D.\nUncommon Friends Endowed Chair Professor in Ethics\n\nFlorida G
 ulf Coast University\nLutgert College of Business\n10501 FGCU Boulevard S.
 \nFort Myers\, FL 33965\n\n239-590-7162\n\n************** Confidentiality 
 Notice ********************\n\nFlorida has a very broad public records law
 .  As a result\, any written communication created or received by Florida 
 Gulf Coast University employees is subject to disclosure to the public and
  the media\, upon request\, unless otherwise exempt.  Under Florida law\, 
 e-mail addresses are public records.  If you do not want your email addres
 s released in response to a public records request\, do not send electroni
 c mail to this entity.  Instead\, contact this office by phone or in writi
 ng.\n\n
