 nNote: For macOS\, Zoom client 5.1.1 or higher is required.\nDesktop Web B
 rowser\nChrome: Within 2 versions of current version\nFirefox: Within 2 ve
 rsions of current version\nEdge: Within 2 versions of current version\nSaf
 ari: Within 2 versions of current version\nProcessor and RAM\nDual-core 2G
 hz or higher (Intel i3/i5/i7 or AMD equivalent)\, 4GB RAM\nBandwidth for W
 ebinar\nFor screen sharing with video thumbnail: 50-150kbps (down)\nHigh-D
 PI support\nZoom desktop client for Windows\, macOS\, or Linux: Global min
 imum version or higher\nIf available\, a webcam or other camera connected 
 to Zoom that is oriented towards the attendees so the presenters can see t
 he participants.\nHDMI laptop connection to the auditorium system (project
 or and audio speakers). This is backup Zoom access in case the auditorium 
 computer fails\nAC power outlet for Macbook Pro\nUSB-C to HDMI connector f
 or Macbook Pro\nWiFi access credentials (user + password)\nIf possible\, c
 onnect the webcam oriented to the attendees to this computer (we will brin
 g an HD webcam to have for backup and/or to use as the webcam oriented to 
 the attendees)\nThe webcam will have a microphone for attendee questions\n
